    "recap_headline": "Miami Ohio University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "OXFORD, Ohio \u2013\nMiami was shut out by Bowling Green Saturday in a 10-0 decision after a four-run first inning for the Falcons.\nRyan Novak\nand\nCarson Raether\nwere offensive bright spots for the RedHawks, putting up two hits apiece. Miami falls to 12-5 (4-1 MAC) with the loss while Bowling Green moves to 5-11 (2-3 MAC).\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nBowling Green's offense came out early, starting the game off with a walk and four hits to take a 4-0 lead.\nA hit and an error led to two more Falcon runs in the top of the second.\nBowling Green added two more runs in the fourth after a leadoff double, a walk, and and a single to make it 8-0.\nThe RedHawks managed two back-to-back hits and an HBP in the bottom of the fourth to load the bases but were unable to score.\nTwo more hits extended the Bowling Green lead to 9-0 in the seventh. Back-to-back doubles stretched their lead to 10 runs in the eighth.\nMiami was unable to close the gap, resulting in a 10-0 eight-inning loss.\nMIAMI GAME NOTES:\nNovak went 2-for-4.\nRaether went 2-for-3.\nUP NEXT:\nThe RedHawks will look to win the series tomorrow in game three against the Falcons. First pitch is set for 11 a.m."
